ly oper\nating in America. It is the lirst\nI i nternal order to receive a charter\ngranted by a special act of con\ngress. Tne order was founded by\nJudge II. Rathborne, in Washington\ncity on February 19, 1864. Kath\nbovnc lit that time was a clerk in a\ngovernment department, believing\nthat something should be done to heal\nI in a measure the wounde made by th?\ni great civil war conceived the idea of\n1 organizing a society to unite former\njoes. Gathering a few kindred spir\nits he instituted the first Knights of\nPythias lodge.\nThe mtst cherished of all the sa-\ncred relics in the possession of the su\npreme lodge is the little Bible which\nwas used by Founder Rathborne in\nobligating the original members and\ni these associated with them in or\nI ganizing Washington lodge No. 1.\nj Genesis of Pthianism\nI The genesis of Pythian Knighthood\ncfi'trs a wide liol'l fur thought. In\n.-peaking of his great organization,\nSupreme Keeper of Records and Seal\ni Fred K. Wheal ton, has eloquently\nsaid:\n\"Years before Rathbone and his\n'associates came together in the im-\ntia! lodge bearing the name. Knitrhts\nof Pythians, the Irish poet and nov\nelist, John 1'anim, had (in 1821)\nimmortalized the story of the great\nest example ot human friendship\nthat ever existed between two men\nsince the dawn of the earth's crea\ntion. Damon and Pythias, by and\nmrougn tne drrrm: -.yhkh bears their\nnarres, have become known through-\ncut the civilized world is cnamplars\nof true friendship. These ancient\nprototypes were students under thr\ndisciples of the learned and scholariv.\nj I ytiiagoras whose genius measures\nBirmingham, Ala., Feb. 21 Ser\nseant Glc.'.n R. Stephens, Alabama\nnational guardsman, will be place;!\non trial st Hamilton, Alabama today\non an inuiotmu'.t charging compli\ncity in the lynching of William\nBand, at Jasper, in Wtilker county\nJanuary 13.\nStephens will be the second of nine\nindicted guardsmen to be placed on\ntrial, and the eyes of the public